<subSubSection id="5AED0642015446981BB692D6FF8C7C1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4C4745318B605DE99538AB246C03D983" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BAE8ED8231ACF53B2BA022E9AC1639B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Chiapas, Oaxaca, Tabasco, Veracruz), Guatemala (Alta Verapaz, 
<normalizedToken id="04F191F2A6E9E21B435004127AF52436" originalValue="Petén">Peten</normalizedToken>
), and Belize (El Cayo), in high forest, lower montane rain forest, and tropical moist forest, often on limestone ridges or in canyons, sometimes near streams, 200-1000 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F5BDED2BCFAEA729D08CD69543D09B1C" captionStart="Figure 45" captionStartId="F45" captionText="Figure 45. Map of geographic distribution of L. gorgonea based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure45" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480057" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
